{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I'm here to spread the word about the"},{"time":3000,"text":"magnificence of spiders"},{"time":5000,"text":"and how much we can learn from them."},{"time":8000,"text":"Spiders are truly global citizens."},{"time":10000,"text":"You can find spiders in nearly"},{"time":12000,"text":"every terrestrial habitat."},{"time":14000,"text":"This red dot marks"},{"time":16000,"text":"the Great Basin of North America,"},{"time":18000,"text":"and I'm involved with an alpine biodiversity"},{"time":20000,"text":"project there with some collaborators."},{"time":22000,"text":"Here's one of our field sites,"},{"time":24000,"text":"and just to give you a sense of perspective,"},{"time":26000,"text":"this little blue smudge here,"},{"time":28000,"text":"that's one of my collaborators."},{"time":30000,"text":"This is a rugged and barren landscape,"},{"time":33000,"text":"yet there are quite a few spiders here."},{"time":35000,"text":"Turning rocks over revealed this crab spider"},{"time":39000,"text":"grappling with a beetle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41000,"text":"Spiders are not just everywhere,"},{"time":44000,"text":"but they're extremely diverse."},{"time":46000,"text":"There are over 40,000 described species"},{"time":49000,"text":"of spiders."},{"time":50000,"text":"To put that number into perspective,"},{"time":52000,"text":"here's a graph comparing the 40,000"},{"time":54000,"text":"species of spiders"},{"time":56000,"text":"to the 400 species of primates."},{"time":58000,"text":"There are two orders of magnitude more"},{"time":60000,"text":"spiders than primates."},{"time":62000,"text":"Spiders are also extremely old."},{"time":66000,"text":"On the bottom here,"},{"time":68000,"text":"this is the geologic timescale,"},{"time":70000,"text":"and the numbers on it indicate millions"},{"time":72000,"text":"of years from the present, so the zero here,"},{"time":74000,"text":"that would be today."},{"time":76000,"text":"So what this figure shows is that spiders"},{"time":79000,"text":"date back to almost 380 million years."},{"time":83000,"text":"To put that into perspective, this red"},{"time":85000,"text":"vertical bar here marks the divergence time"},{"time":88000,"text":"of humans from chimpanzees,"},{"time":91000,"text":"a mere seven million years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94000,"text":"All spiders make silk"},{"time":96000,"text":"at some point in their life."},{"time":98000,"text":"Most spiders use copious amounts of silk,"},{"time":101000,"text":"and silk is essential to their survival"},{"time":103000,"text":"and reproduction."},{"time":105000,"text":"Even fossil spiders can make silk,"},{"time":107000,"text":"as we can see from this impression of"},{"time":109000,"text":"a spinneret on this fossil spider."},{"time":112000,"text":"So this means that both spiders"},{"time":114000,"text":"and spider silk have been around"},{"time":116000,"text":"for 380 million years."},{"time":121000,"text":"It doesn't take long from working with spiders"},{"time":124000,"text":"to start noticing how essential silk is"},{"time":127000,"text":"to just about every aspect of their life."},{"time":130000,"text":"Spiders use silk for many purposes, including"},{"time":133000,"text":"the trailing safety dragline,"},{"time":135000,"text":"wrapping eggs for reproduction,"},{"time":138000,"text":"protective retreats"},{"time":140000,"text":"and catching prey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142000,"text":"There are many kinds of spider silk."},{"time":144000,"text":"For example, this garden spider can make"},{"time":147000,"text":"seven different kinds of silks."},{"time":149000,"text":"When you look at this orb web, you're actually"},{"time":151000,"text":"seeing many types of silk fibers."},{"time":154000,"text":"The frame and radii of this web"},{"time":156000,"text":"is made up of one type of silk,"},{"time":159000,"text":"while the capture spiral is a composite"},{"time":161000,"text":"of two different silks:"},{"time":163000,"text":"the filament and the sticky droplet."},{"time":166000,"text":"How does an individual spider"},{"time":169000,"text":"make so many kinds of silk?"},{"time":172000,"text":"To answer that, you have to look a lot closer"},{"time":174000,"text":"at the spinneret region of a spider."},{"time":176000,"text":"So silk comes out of the spinnerets, and for"},{"time":178000,"text":"those of us spider silk biologists, this is what"},{"time":180000,"text":"we call the \"business end\" of the spider. (Laughter)"},{"time":182000,"text":"We spend long days ..."},{"time":184000,"text":"Hey! Don't laugh. That's my life."},{"time":186000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":188000,"text":"We spend long days and nights"},{"time":190000,"text":"staring at this part of the spider."},{"time":193000,"text":"And this is what we see."},{"time":195000,"text":"You can see multiple fibers"},{"time":197000,"text":"coming out of the spinnerets, because"},{"time":200000,"text":"each spinneret has many spigots on it."},{"time":203000,"text":"Each of these silk fibers exits from the spigot,"},{"time":206000,"text":"and if you were to trace the fiber back"},{"time":208000,"text":"into the spider, what you would find is that"},{"time":211000,"text":"each spigot connects to its own individual"},{"time":213000,"text":"silk gland. A silk gland kind of looks like a sac"},{"time":216000,"text":"with a lot of silk proteins stuck inside."},{"time":219000,"text":"So if you ever have the opportunity to dissect"},{"time":221000,"text":"an orb-web-weaving spider,"},{"time":223000,"text":"and I hope you do,"},{"time":225000,"text":"what you would find is a bounty"},{"time":228000,"text":"of beautiful, translucent silk glands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231000,"text":"Inside each spider, there are hundreds"},{"time":233000,"text":"of silk glands, sometimes thousands."},{"time":236000,"text":"These can be grouped into seven categories."},{"time":239000,"text":"They differ by size, shape,"},{"time":241000,"text":"and sometimes even color."},{"time":243000,"text":"In an orb-web-weaving spider,"},{"time":245000,"text":"you can find seven types of silk glands,"},{"time":247000,"text":"and what I have depicted here in this picture,"},{"time":249000,"text":"let's start at the one o'clock position,"},{"time":252000,"text":"there's tubuliform silk glands, which are used"},{"time":254000,"text":"to make the outer silk of an egg sac."},{"time":256000,"text":"There's the aggregate and flagelliform silk"},{"time":258000,"text":"glands which combine to make the sticky"},{"time":260000,"text":"capture spiral of an orb web."},{"time":263000,"text":"Pyriform silk glands make the attachment"},{"time":265000,"text":"cement -- that's the silk that's used to adhere"},{"time":268000,"text":"silk lines to a substrate."},{"time":271000,"text":"There's also aciniform silk,"},{"time":273000,"text":"which is used to wrap prey."},{"time":275000,"text":"Minor ampullate silk is used in web construction."},{"time":277000,"text":"And the most studied silk line"},{"time":279000,"text":"of them all: major ampullate silk."},{"time":281000,"text":"This is the silk that's used to make the frame"},{"time":283000,"text":"and radii of an orb web, and also"},{"time":286000,"text":"the safety trailing dragline."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289000,"text":"But what, exactly, is spider silk?"},{"time":293000,"text":"Spider silk is almost entirely protein."},{"time":296000,"text":"Nearly all of these proteins can be explained"},{"time":298000,"text":"by a single gene family,"},{"time":301000,"text":"so this means that the diversity of silk types"},{"time":303000,"text":"we see today is encoded by one gene family,"},{"time":308000,"text":"so presumably the original spider ancestor"},{"time":311000,"text":"made one kind of silk,"},{"time":313000,"text":"and over the last 380 million years,"},{"time":316000,"text":"that one silk gene has duplicated"},{"time":319000,"text":"and then diverged, specialized,"},{"time":322000,"text":"over and over and over again, to get"},{"time":325000,"text":"the large variety of flavors of spider silks"},{"time":327000,"text":"that we have today."},{"time":330000,"text":"There are several features that all these silks"},{"time":332000,"text":"have in common. They all have a common"},{"time":334000,"text":"design, such as they're all very long --"},{"time":336000,"text":"they're sort of outlandishly long"},{"time":339000,"text":"compared to other proteins."},{"time":341000,"text":"They're very repetitive, and they're very rich"},{"time":344000,"text":"in the amino acids glycine and alanine."},{"time":347000,"text":"To give you an idea of what"},{"time":349000,"text":"a spider silk protein looks like,"},{"time":351000,"text":"this is a dragline silk protein,"},{"time":353000,"text":"it's just a portion of it,"},{"time":355000,"text":"from the black widow spider."},{"time":357000,"text":"This is the kind of sequence that I love"},{"time":359000,"text":"looking at day and night. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":362000,"text":"So what you're seeing here is the one letter"},{"time":364000,"text":"abbreviation for amino acids, and I've colored"},{"time":366000,"text":"in the glycines with green,"},{"time":368000,"text":"and the alanines in red, and so"},{"time":370000,"text":"you can see it's just a lot of G's and A's."},{"time":373000,"text":"You can also see that there's a lot of short"},{"time":376000,"text":"sequence motifs that repeat over and over"},{"time":379000,"text":"and over again, so for example there's a lot of"},{"time":381000,"text":"what we call polyalanines, or iterated A's,"},{"time":384000,"text":"AAAAA. There's GGQ. There's GGY."},{"time":388000,"text":"You can think of these short motifs"},{"time":390000,"text":"that repeat over and over again as words,"},{"time":393000,"text":"and these words occur in sentences."},{"time":396000,"text":"So for example this would be one sentence,"},{"time":399000,"text":"and you would get this sort of green region"},{"time":401000,"text":"and the red polyalanine, that repeats"},{"time":403000,"text":"over and over and over again,"},{"time":405000,"text":"and you can have that hundreds and"},{"time":407000,"text":"hundreds and hundreds of times within"},{"time":409000,"text":"an individual silk molecule."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411000,"text":"Silks made by the same spider can have"},{"time":413000,"text":"dramatically different repeat sequences."},{"time":416000,"text":"At the top of the screen, you're seeing"},{"time":419000,"text":"the repeat unit from the dragline silk"},{"time":422000,"text":"of a garden argiope spider."},{"time":425000,"text":"It's short. And on the bottom,"},{"time":427000,"text":"this is the repeat sequence for the"},{"time":429000,"text":"egg case, or tubuliform silk protein,"},{"time":431000,"text":"for the exact same spider. And you can see"},{"time":434000,"text":"how dramatically different"},{"time":436000,"text":"these silk proteins are -- so this is"},{"time":439000,"text":"sort of the beauty of the diversification"},{"time":441000,"text":"of the spider silk gene family."},{"time":443000,"text":"You can see that the repeat units differ"},{"time":445000,"text":"in length. They also differ in sequence."},{"time":447000,"text":"So I've colored in the glycines again"},{"time":449000,"text":"in green, alanine in red, and the serines,"},{"time":452000,"text":"the letter S, in purple. And you can see"},{"time":455000,"text":"that the top repeat unit can be explained"},{"time":457000,"text":"almost entirely by green and red,"},{"time":460000,"text":"and the bottom repeat unit has"},{"time":462000,"text":"a substantial amount of purple."},{"time":464000,"text":"What silk biologists do is we try to relate"},{"time":467000,"text":"these sequences, these amino acid"},{"time":469000,"text":"sequences, to the mechanical properties"},{"time":471000,"text":"of the silk fibers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473000,"text":"Now, it's really convenient that spiders use their silk"},{"time":476000,"text":"completely outside their body."},{"time":478000,"text":"This makes testing spider silk really, really"},{"time":480000,"text":"easy to do in the laboratory, because"},{"time":482000,"text":"we're actually, you know, testing it in air"},{"time":485000,"text":"that's exactly the environment that"},{"time":487000,"text":"spiders are using their silk proteins."},{"time":489000,"text":"So this makes quantifying silk properties by"},{"time":491000,"text":"methods such as tensile testing, which is"},{"time":493000,"text":"basically, you know, tugging on one end"},{"time":495000,"text":"of the fiber, very amenable."},{"time":498000,"text":"Here are stress-strain curves"},{"time":501000,"text":"generated by tensile testing"},{"time":503000,"text":"five fibers made by the same spider."},{"time":506000,"text":"So what you can see here is that"},{"time":509000,"text":"the five fibers have different behaviors."},{"time":512000,"text":"Specifically, if you look on the vertical axis,"},{"time":514000,"text":"that's stress. If you look at the maximum"},{"time":517000,"text":"stress value for each of these fibers,"},{"time":519000,"text":"you can see that there's a lot of variation,"},{"time":522000,"text":"and in fact dragline, or major ampullate silk,"},{"time":525000,"text":"is the strongest of these fibers."},{"time":527000,"text":"We think that's because the dragline silk,"},{"time":530000,"text":"which is used to make the frame and radii"},{"time":533000,"text":"for a web, needs to be very strong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535000,"text":"On the other hand, if you were to look at"},{"time":537000,"text":"strain -- this is how much a fiber can be"},{"time":539000,"text":"extended -- if you look at the maximum value"},{"time":541000,"text":"here, again, there's a lot of variation"},{"time":544000,"text":"and the clear winner is flagelliform,"},{"time":546000,"text":"or the capture spiral filament."},{"time":548000,"text":"In fact, this flagelliform fiber can"},{"time":550000,"text":"actually stretch over twice its original length."},{"time":554000,"text":"So silk fibers vary in their strength"},{"time":557000,"text":"and also their extensibility."},{"time":559000,"text":"In the case of the capture spiral,"},{"time":561000,"text":"it needs to be so stretchy to absorb"},{"time":563000,"text":"the impact of flying prey."},{"time":565000,"text":"If it wasn't able to stretch so much, then"},{"time":567000,"text":"basically when an insect hit the web,"},{"time":569000,"text":"it would just trampoline right off of it."},{"time":571000,"text":"So if the web was made entirely out of"},{"time":573000,"text":"dragline silk, an insect is very likely to just"},{"time":576000,"text":"bounce right off. But by having really, really"},{"time":578000,"text":"stretchy capture spiral silk, the web is actually"},{"time":580000,"text":"able to absorb the impact"},{"time":582000,"text":"of that intercepted prey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"There's quite a bit of variation within"},{"time":587000,"text":"the fibers that an individual spider can make."},{"time":590000,"text":"We call that the tool kit of a spider."},{"time":593000,"text":"That's what the spider has"},{"time":595000,"text":"to interact with their environment."},{"time":597000,"text":"But how about variation among spider"},{"time":599000,"text":"species, so looking at one type of silk"},{"time":601000,"text":"and looking at different species of spiders?"},{"time":604000,"text":"This is an area that's largely unexplored"},{"time":606000,"text":"but here's a little bit of data I can show you."},{"time":610000,"text":"This is the comparison of the toughness"},{"time":612000,"text":"of the dragline spilk spun"},{"time":614000,"text":"by 21 species of spiders."},{"time":616000,"text":"Some of them are orb-weaving spiders and"},{"time":618000,"text":"some of them are non-orb-weaving spiders."},{"time":621000,"text":"It's been hypothesized that"},{"time":623000,"text":"orb-weaving spiders, like this argiope here,"},{"time":626000,"text":"should have the toughest dragline silks"},{"time":628000,"text":"because they must intercept flying prey."},{"time":631000,"text":"What you see here on this toughness graph"},{"time":634000,"text":"is the higher the black dot is on the graph,"},{"time":636000,"text":"the higher the toughness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638000,"text":"The 21 species are indicated here by this"},{"time":641000,"text":"phylogeny, this evolutionary tree, that shows"},{"time":644000,"text":"their genetic relationships, and I've colored"},{"time":646000,"text":"in yellow the orb-web-weaving spiders."},{"time":649000,"text":"If you look right here at the two red arrows,"},{"time":652000,"text":"they point to the toughness values"},{"time":655000,"text":"for the draglines of nephila clavipes and"},{"time":657000,"text":"araneus diadematus."},{"time":659000,"text":"These are the two species of spiders"},{"time":661000,"text":"for which the vast majority of time and money"},{"time":664000,"text":"on synthetic spider silk research has been"},{"time":667000,"text":"to replicate their dragline silk proteins."},{"time":670000,"text":"Yet, their draglines are not the toughest."},{"time":674000,"text":"In fact, the toughest dragline in this survey"},{"time":677000,"text":"is this one right here in this white region,"},{"time":680000,"text":"a non orb-web-weaving spider."},{"time":682000,"text":"This is the dragline spun by scytodes,"},{"time":684000,"text":"the spitting spider."},{"time":686000,"text":"Scytodes doesn't use a web at all"},{"time":689000,"text":"to catch prey. Instead, scytodes"},{"time":691000,"text":"sort of lurks around and waits for prey"},{"time":694000,"text":"to get close to it, and then immobilizes prey"},{"time":697000,"text":"by spraying a silk-like venom onto that insect."},{"time":701000,"text":"Think of hunting with silly string."},{"time":704000,"text":"That's how scytodes forages."},{"time":707000,"text":"We don't really know why scytodes"},{"time":709000,"text":"needs such a tough dragline,"},{"time":712000,"text":"but it's unexpected results like this that make"},{"time":715000,"text":"bio-prospecting so exciting and worthwhile."},{"time":719000,"text":"It frees us from the constraints"},{"time":721000,"text":"of our imagination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":723000,"text":"Now I'm going to mark on"},{"time":725000,"text":"the toughness values for nylon fiber,"},{"time":728000,"text":"bombyx -- or domesticated silkworm silk --"},{"time":731000,"text":"wool, Kevlar, and carbon fibers."},{"time":734000,"text":"And what you can see is that nearly"},{"time":736000,"text":"all the spider draglines surpass them."},{"time":738000,"text":"It's the combination of strength, extensibility"},{"time":742000,"text":"and toughness that makes spider silk so"},{"time":745000,"text":"special, and that has attracted the attention"},{"time":748000,"text":"of biomimeticists, so people that turn"},{"time":751000,"text":"to nature to try to find new solutions."},{"time":754000,"text":"And the strength, extensibility and toughness"},{"time":757000,"text":"of spider silks combined with the fact that"},{"time":760000,"text":"silks do not elicit an immune response,"},{"time":763000,"text":"have attracted a lot of interest in the use"},{"time":766000,"text":"of spider silks in biomedical applications,"},{"time":768000,"text":"for example, as a component of"},{"time":770000,"text":"artificial tendons, for serving as"},{"time":773000,"text":"guides to regrow nerves, and for"},{"time":777000,"text":"scaffolds for tissue growth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":780000,"text":"Spider silks also have a lot of potential"},{"time":783000,"text":"for their anti-ballistic capabilities."},{"time":785000,"text":"Silks could be incorporated into body"},{"time":787000,"text":"and equipment armor that would be more"},{"time":790000,"text":"lightweight and flexible"},{"time":792000,"text":"than any armor available today."},{"time":795000,"text":"In addition to these biomimetic"},{"time":798000,"text":"applications of spider silks,"},{"time":800000,"text":"personally, I find studying spider silks"},{"time":804000,"text":"just fascinating in and of itself."},{"time":807000,"text":"I love when I'm in the laboratory,"},{"time":811000,"text":"a new spider silk sequence comes in."},{"time":814000,"text":"That's just the best. (Laughter)"},{"time":817000,"text":"It's like the spiders are sharing"},{"time":820000,"text":"an ancient secret with me, and that's why"},{"time":822000,"text":"I'm going to spend the rest of my life"},{"time":824000,"text":"studying spider silk."},{"time":826000,"text":"The next time you see a spider web,"},{"time":829000,"text":"please, pause and look a little closer."},{"time":832000,"text":"You'll be seeing one of the most"},{"time":834000,"text":"high-performance materials known to man."},{"time":837000,"text":"To borrow from the writings"},{"time":839000,"text":"of a spider named Charlotte,"},{"time":842000,"text":"silk is terrific."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844000,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":847000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}